June 17 at 9:57 PM ·

The Southeast High School Class of 2020 Commencement Ceremony will be held this Saturday, June 20th at 7:00 p.m.

Due to this being a closed/ticketed event with limited attendance, the event will also be live-streamed on this USD 247 Southeast Lancers Facebook page. Please share this information with any family/friends who do not have a ticket to attend in person, so they can tune in and watch the live video.

A friendly reminder for those who will be attending the ceremony in person, please abide by the recommended social distancing guidelines. Masks are encouraged.

Please be patient and respectful as the USD 247 staff members are working hard to make this event happen safely.

Congratulations to the Class of 2020! We are excited to honor you on Saturday!

Eastern Kansas Sports
October 28, 2019 at 4:08 PM ·

Thank you to Jennifer Gardner for passing this along to us for USD 247 Southeast Lancers fans traveling to Osage City:
"For those coming to the Cherokee-Southeast vs Osage City game...the football stadium is on the southwest corner of town. We have some construction, but if you turn (head west) at Sonic, it'll take you through town and at the stop sign you turn left. We have a large parking lot and some parking near the visitors' side, too. Hope this helps, I know I hate not knowing where I'm going in a new town.

We do have a Sonic, Subway (west), Casey's (deli, etc, near Sonic), Pizza Hut (construction area), Buzzards Pizza (by Sonic), Marilyn's (burgers, steaks, etc, east side), Ridge Iron Grill (downtown and not blocked by construction), El Ranchito (west side by Subway), Jade Garden (west), plus the concession stand (usually burgers, hotdogs, walking tacos, etc)"

post_text:
Southeast Booster Club Membership Drive!
Please take the time to sign up for a 2019/2020 Booster Club Membership. This year we will once again have t-shirts with your membership. The cost of a membership is $50.00 per family which includes one t-shirt. Additional t-shirts are available for purchase for anyone that is interested. If you would like to sign up please let Josh Jacobs or Sis Renn know, and we will get you signed up. Booster Club membership fees are used throughout the year for all sports and student activities at SHS such as help providing meals and other items needed.

Sports in Kansas
February 16, 2019 at 10:22 PM ·

Coach Dan Wall of Southeast Cherokee won his 600th career game Friday night against Marmaton Valley 67-35. He was the head coach of Independence Community College when they won the national JUCO championship in the late 70’s. And he also won a state championship at Field Kindley High School. #sportsinkansas

post_text:
Want to thank all the students, parents and teams for making this another great Southeast Booster Club Youth Basketball Tournament. With 27 teams entered and 41 games played over Saturday and Sunday everything ran great thanks to everyone's help.

Could not have done it without everyone's help. When we host events like this it reminds us how good of kids we have in our district. Every athlete that signed up to work showed up on time and was very respectful and polite to all the teams and coaches. They all worked great with the refs and also stuck around to help cleanup when asked.

Southeast High School Booster Club

Sports in Kansas
October 8, 2018 at 9:34 AM ·

Craw-Kan Telephone Cooperative Inc. Team of the Week from Southeast Kansas: Southeast-Cherokee football entered the year on a 28-game losing streak that dated back to 2014. The Lancers are now 4-2 with a rushing attack of 288 yards per game. QB Brett Malle has over 900 yards of offense while Zaden Hendricks & Jakob Tavernaro each have 360+ yards rushing & each lead the team in tackles w/ 41. Huge turnaround for a program that didn't score over 12 points in a game last year and were shutout in nearly half of their games. #sportsinkansas

Lancer Softball Players Receive State Honorable Mention

USD 247 Southeast Lancers
July 16, 2018 at 3:37 PM ·

Four Southeast Lancer softball players received State recognition in a recent release of the 2018 Kansas 3A All-State Softball Team. Laura Ridings (senior), Megan Colvin (junior), Katie Bitner (sophomore), and McKenna Renn (sophomore) each earned Honorable Mention in a release from Sports in Kansas. Selections were finalized by Sports in Kansas with input from several media outlets in Kansas. Input was taken from coaches and athletic director nomination forms sent in to Sports in Kansas following the 2018 season. [ 29 more words ]
